man man - obtains detailed documentation about commands
q- Exits the manual page
mv- moves or renames files and directories
chmod- modifies the file permissions
chown- changes the ownership of a file
dd- copies data from input to output
pwd- Displays the current working directory
ps- list the processes that are currently running in the system
su- simulates a login as another user or becomes a superuser
sudo- Runs a command as a superuser by default or another named user
grep- used to search for specific strings of characters within a file or other command output
ifconfig- used to display or configure network card-related information
apt-get- used to install, configure, and remove packages on Debian and its derivatives
lwconfig- used to display and configure wireless network card related information
shutdown- shuts down the virtual machine
passwd- changes the password
cat- lists the contents of a file
ls- Displays the files inside a directory
cd- changes the current directory
mkdir- creates directories
touch- creates text files
cp- Copies files and directories from a source to a destination
rm- removes files or directories
cd ~ changes the directory to the home directory
> represents redirection
>> appends data to the end of the referred file, keeping the current content intact.

